ntsb4132txt-1-5-5-0-3 On September 1, 2001, at 1645 central daylight time, an experimental Spears RV-6, N910RS, was destroyed by impact forces and subsequent ground fire about 1 mile west of Campbell Airport (C81), Grayslake, Illinois. 
ntsb4132txt-1-5-5-0-4 The airplane departed controlled flight prior to ground impact. 
ntsb4132txt-1-5-5-0-5 The private pilot received fatal injuries. 
ntsb4132txt-1-5-5-0-6 The 14 CFR Part 91 personal flight had originated from Roanoke, Texas, with C81 as the intended final destination. 
ntsb4132txt-1-5-5-0-7 It is unknown where the airplane had last landed for refueling prior to proceeding to C81. 
ntsb4132txt-1-5-5-0-8 Visual meteorological conditions prevailed. 
ntsb4132txt-1-5-5-0-9 No flight plan was filed. 
ntsb4132txt-1-5-5-0-10 A witness reported the airplane was flying at about 500 feet above ground level (agl) and was circling towards the airport when the airplane "barreled" left, recover, and then the nose of the airplane went straight down. 
ntsb4132txt-1-5-5-0-11 Another witness reported seeing the airplane circling before the airplane nose dived into the terrain. 
